  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "The previous forks didn't have child evm objects. Whenever an error would occur, I'd empty `accounts_to_delete`. eg. [evm.accounts_to_delete = set()](https://github.com/ethereum/execution-specs/blob/f037baf28cc7c546f9600fb1db91e71fba32ac88/src/ethereum/tangerine_whistle/vm/interpreter.py#L126) and the parent would collect the childs `accounts_to_delete` eg. [evm.accounts_to_delete.update(child_evm.accounts_to_delete)\r\n](https://github.com/ethereum/execution-specs/blob/f037baf28cc7c546f9600fb1db91e71fba32ac88/src/ethereum/tangerine_whistle/vm/instructions/system.py#L241)\r\nHowever, now that the evm objects have children, it felt silly to me that the parent stores the `accounts_to_delete` of the child. \r\nThis also applies to other things like `logs`, `refund_counter `.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nIn order to get a clean diff, I propose we add children to the previous forks too and then port `collect_accounts_to_delete`. Thoughts?\r\n\r\nI can do this in a separate PR.\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @voith in https://github.com/ethereum/execution-specs/pull/423#r790635612_",
